{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43513","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43513/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43513/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43513/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/43513","id":1086305866,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM4wKF5W","number":43513,"title":"Covariance support for @NamedTuple","user":{"login":"o314","id":4026002,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwMjYwMDI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4026002?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314","html_url":"https://github.com/o314","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/o314/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2021-12-21T23:23:27Z","updated_at":"2022-01-05T23:19:21Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/43513","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/43513","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/43513.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/43513.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"With @NamedTuple, one can code
```julia
using Test
@test (a=1,b=true) isa NamedTuple{(:a,:b),Tuple{Int,Bool}}
```
by shortening it with
```julia
@test (a=1,b=true) isa @NamedTuple{a::Int, b::Bool}
```
but this fails with, for example, a nullable type
```julia
@test_broken (a=1,b=true) isa @NamedTuple{a::Int, b::Union{Bool,Nothing}}
# logical since it expands to :
@test_broken (a=1,b=true) isa NamedTuple{(:a,:b),Tuple{Int,Union{Bool,Nothing}}}
# namedtuple covariance is not handled. this is what we are looking for
@test (a=1,b=true) isa NamedTuple{(:a,:b),<:Tuple{Int,Union{Bool,Nothing}}}
```
This PR propose to make it work, by adding a `<:` recognition
```julia
@test (a=1,b=true) isa @NamedTuple{<:(a::Int, b::Union{Bool,Nothing})}
```
